From phgrosjean at sciviews.org  Wed May  5 21:37:03 2010
From: phgrosjean at sciviews.org (Philippe Grosjean)
Date: Wed, 05 May 2010 21:37:03 +0200
Subject: [R-sig-teaching] Creating table from data.frame
In-Reply-To: <4BE156E1.B080.00B1.0@gw.muhlenberg.edu>
References: <4BE156E1.B080.00B1.0@gw.muhlenberg.edu>
Message-ID: <4BE1C8DF.9030401@sciviews.org>

This is easy:

# Recode gender
levels(x$gender) <- c("men", "women")
# Build the two-way table (and print it)
(x.Table <- xtabs(count ~ status + gender, data = x))

Best,

PhG

